OL,3,CFly-tipping: Farmers facing
OL,4,C'continuous battle' of dumped waste
OL,6,FA Berkshire farmer is among the
OL,7,Fhundreds facing the "continuous
OL,8,Fbattle" of dealing with illegally
OL,9,Fdumped waste.
OL,11,FTyres, fridge freezers, white goods,
OL,12,Fand bags of concrete, bricks and
OL,13,Frubble are among the items William
OL,14,FWestacott comes across, dumped at
OL,15,Fentrances around his family-run farm.
OL,17,FHe's also dealing with general
OL,18,Fhousehold rubbish being fly-tipped on
OL,19,Fhis land, including cans and bottles.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
