FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1772062286
OL,3,CFly-tipping: Farmers facing
OL,4,C'continuous battle' of dumped waste
OL,6,FWilliam said: "As soon as you've
OL,7,Fcleared up one episode, within a
OL,8,Fcouple of weeks, you're having to deal
OL,9,Fwith the next episode.
OL,11,F"It's a continuous battle which is
OL,12,Fdetrimental to many aspects of my
OL,13,Fbusiness - be it the quality of the
OL,14,Fsoil that the crops rely on, to the
OL,15,Fwild habitats that it is polluting."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1772062286
OL,3,CFly-tipping: Farmers facing
OL,4,C'continuous battle' of dumped waste
OL,6,FHe added: "It's a drain on time and
OL,7,Fresources when there are many others
OL,8,Fthings we would rather be doing. But
OL,9,Fwe have to clear it up to make sure
OL,10,Fthe farm is clear of litter and that I
OL,11,Fcan safely use the farm entrances into
OL,12,Fthe fields."
OL,14,FNew figures released on Wednesday (25
OL,15,FFebruary) reveal local authorities in
OL,16,FEngland recorded a 9% rise in fly-
OL,17,Ftipping incidents in 2024/2025 - from
OL,18,Fthe 1.15 million they had to deal with
OL,19,Fin 2023/2024.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1772062286
OL,3,CFly-tipping: Farmers facing
OL,4,C'continuous battle' of dumped waste
OL,6,FIn the South East there were 109,015
OL,7,Frecorded fly tips - with incidents up
OL,8,Fby 70.9% in Reading, 40% in Sevenoaks
OL,9,Fand an increase of 20.6% in Crawley.
OL,11,FThe figures from the Environment
OL,12,FDepartment (Defra) relate to rubbish
OL,13,Fillegally dumped on public land.
OL,15,FHowever when it is private land,
OL,16,Ffarmers like Mr Westacott are having
OL,17,Fto foot the bill for the clear-up.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
