OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1772062286
OL,3,CFly-tipping: Farmers facing
OL,4,C'continuous battle' of dumped waste
OL,6,FThe government says it is making
OL,7,Faround #78 billion available to
OL,8,Fcouncil budgets in England this year
OL,9,Fto help fund key responsibilities like
OL,10,Ffly-tipping.
OL,12,FConvicted fly-tippers can receive a
OL,13,Ffine, a community sentence or a prison
OL,14,Fsentence.
OL,16,FMoney raised from fly-tipping funds is
OL,17,Fused by councils to clean up land
OL,18,Fimpacted by waste dumping.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
